Got it — you want me to add soundnessup so it’s automatically installed and ready every time your Codespace starts, on top of the Rust + Node + Docker setup.

Here’s the updated devcontainer.json you can use:

{
  "name": "Rust + Node + Docker + Soundness Dev",
  "image": "mcr.microsoft.com/devcontainers/rust:latest",

  "features": {
    "ghcr.io/devcontainers/features/node:1": {
      "version": "lts"
    },
    "ghcr.io/devcontainers/features/docker-in-docker:2": {
      "version": "latest"
    }
  },

  "customizations": {
    "vscode": {
      "extensions": [
        "rust-lang.rust-analyzer",
        "ms-azuretools.vscode-docker",
        "ms-vscode.cpptools",
        "esbenp.prettier-vscode"
      ]
    }
  },

  "remoteUser": "vscode",

  "postCreateCommand": "curl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/soundnesslabs/soundness-layer/main/soundnessup/install | bash && source ~/.bashrc && soundnessup install && soundnessup update && rustc --version && cargo --version && node --version && npm --version",

  "mounts": [
    "source=/var/run/docker.sock,target=/var/run/docker.sock,type=bind"
  ]
}


---

How to set it up

1. In your repo:



mkdir -p .devcontainer
nano .devcontainer/devcontainer.json

2. Paste the file above and save.


3. Commit:



git add .devcontainer
git commit -m "Add Rust + Node + Docker + Soundness devcontainer"
git push

4. Close and reopen your Codespace.
It will now:



Preinstall Rust, Cargo, Node.js, Docker

Automatically install and update soundnessup

Load all tools on startup, no manual setup.



